  "response": "John Williams did not compose the full score for Rogue One: A Star Wars Story because the film was a standalone story outside of the main Skywalker saga. Alexandre Desplat was originally hired to compose the soundtrack, but due to scheduling conflicts, Michael Giacchino ultimately composed the final score. However, Williams did contribute the main Star Wars theme, which appears in the film. Giacchino worked to create a score that honored the musical style of the Star Wars universe while bringing his own unique approach to the film.",
